			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">No thanks.
<br />

<br />
We don't need 1 big ferocious all powerful pet, or even a mini-ferocious one.   <img src="images/smiles/eusa_hand.gif" alt="Speak to the hand" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
First off, Mages have 4 lines of pets at our disposal to use.  This is part of our pet advantage. Each pet fills a niche, and performs a specialized task for us.  As we gain levels the pets themselves become more distinct in their particular task.  I, for one, feel that our level 60+ pets could use some furthur amplification in their various tasks, which could be included in some future "balancing" patches.
<br />

<br />
What I'd like to see.
<br />

<br />
Rathe's Son - Get some furthur boost in AC/Mitigation/HP.  This would be our solo'ing pet for high level (Tier 2 and above), and also for times when a group needs an off tank to control adds.
<br />

<br />
Servant of Marr - This should be our long term DPS pet all the way.  I'd love to see this pet giving us continuous 125 DPS in a backstabbing position (hasted of course).
<br />

<br />
Ward of Xegony - A solo or group pet to use when stuns are needed (for casters especially).  This pet should be a good all around pet in terms of DPS and tanking.  For times when both are needed.
<br />

<br />
Child of Ro - A very situational pet, perhaps for quick fights that last less than 2 minutes, or just about any fight where you have a suspended pet to bring out when Sparky runs dry on mana.  I think they should really  finish what they started with Sparky and totally convert him to a wizard that doesn't melee just nukes until out of mana then sits and meds back to full.  Would be nice to see Sparky's mana bar too (how hard would that be to implement?).  At least then we could gauge how he's doing and how buffs are affecting him.  Would like to see some better nukes from this fella for some real quick burst damage.  And to prevent people from just casting another Sparky when the first is dry of mana, make the recast time like 20 minutes.  If this is too hard to code then I'd understand, so just forget about him and focus on the other pets.
<br />

<br />
Monster Summoning IV - Raid oriented pet with great survivability in raids.  Should be highly resistant to AOE spells with (a better type?) of Prism skin and above average DPS.  For any raid / boss encounter where Servant would be cut to ribbons before the fight was halfway over.  Would like to see the stun component removed and exchanged with a better Prism skin or some other idea that helps it survive raid encounters. 
<br />

<br />
What I'd love to see is all these pets fine-tuned as detailed above to be better able to do their specific function, and really cement our class as the true pet masters.  Beastlords would still have their all around tough warders with their 50 different buffs that make them proc like hell and our easily obtainable pet toys.  And with their 65% slow they would still be valued in many groups.  
<br />

<br />
Are we or are we not the ultimate summoners of pets?   Doesn't possessing 5 distinctly different types of pets give us right to this claim?  As such, we should be able to find a pet for almost any situation that will excel.  
<br />

<br />

<br />
I know its early but I'm putting all this on my x-mas list.   <img src="images/smiles/alien.gif" alt="alien" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
