				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Are we or are we not the ultimate summoners of pets? Doesn't possessing 5 distinctly different types of pets give us right to this claim? As such, we should be able to find a pet for almost any situation that will excel. </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
personally i think you have it wrong... are we the ultimate summoners?  YES, hands down, NO ONE can summoned even a fraction of the items we can, pets included.  Possessing 5 distinctly different types of pets however DOES NOT directly equivalate to being THE best "PET" class...
<br />

<br />
Beastlords are literally "Lords of Beasts"... Magicians are not Lord of Pets... we are Masters of the Elements, hence why we have so many different kinds of pets.  They are each different, about as different as the many elements we are masters of... this is perfectly fitting in roleplay terms.  I think most magicians have gotten it in their heads that we SHOULD be the Master of the Pets simply because we had the most for the longest amt of time.... Necro and Sk pets dont really hold a candle to ours but now i sense so much hostility toward SOE for creating a truely Pet Based class... 
<br />

<br />
Get over it i say lol, beasts get all those buffs to offset the fact they are mired to 1 and only 1 pet... EVER... ours are honestly still superior IF you know how to use them, so what if they buff thiers more, or make them proc, our weapons give our pets the ability to proc as well.  Honestly are pets are pretty close to on par w/ warders the difference being we get diff types to fit the situation, they do not.
<br />

<br />
If you really wanna gripe about something that doesn't make sense, then write SOE about why as Masters of the Elements we dont have Cold based spells.... period... this is the ONLY thing that doesn't make sense to me, IMO we should get fire/cold more then fire/mag based nukes but that's just me.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=608950" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.divinesilence.shattering.us/sigs/thayetsig.jpg" border="0" /></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
