				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">LOL, that was great Zarath   <img src="images/smiles/eusa_clap.gif" alt="Applause" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
I guess I should clarify something here.  I believe the point of us having 
<br />
as many types of elemental pets as we do is so we are able to use one that most benefits us for every situation in EQ, whether it be solo'ing, grouping, or raiding.  Such a specialized class that we seem to be, as most of our spells revolve around pets,  I do believe we should think of ourselves as the "premier" pet class and as such should have more attention and fine tuning regarding our elementals.
<br />

<br />
So, in essence I see where you are coming from Mistress Thayett, regarding us being able to find a superior pet for any given situation, but again I stress that because we are a very specialized pet class we should get more attention and fine tuning in that area.  If you don't want to offend beastlords by saying it out loud, fine, but I'll still believe us to be "the premier" pet class.
<br />

<br />
